        <num>CC 1743</num>
        <heading>1743.  Universal succession; liability for estate debts</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1743.  Universal succession; liability for estate debts
The donee of a universal or general donation of property that the donor will leave at his death, as a universal successor of the donor, is answerable for the debts of the estate of the donor in accordance with the provisions of Chapter 13 of Title I of Book III.</p>
        </content>
